This single `index.html` file renders a **3D cork** with:

- **LatheGeometry** shaped to the classic wine-cork silhouette — tapered top, bulbous middle, narrower base
- **Procedural cork texture** generated via Canvas 2D — granular noise, cell-like structures, and subtle veins
- **Bump map** for that bumpy, porous cork surface feel
- **Three-point lighting** (key, fill, rim) with soft shadows on a dark ground plane
- **Gentle animation** — slow rotation and a subtle floating bob

Just save it and open in any modern browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>3D Corn</title>
<style>
